Interface λ<R>

  • Type Parameters:
    R - Return type of the function.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CheckedFunction0<R>, CheckedFunction1<T1,R>, CheckedFunction2<T1,T2,R>, CheckedFunction3<T1,T2,T3,R>, CheckedFunction4<T1,T2,T3,T4,R>, CheckedFunction5<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,R>, CheckedFunction6<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,R>, CheckedFunction7<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7,R>, CheckedFunction8<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7,T8,R>, Function0<R>, Function1<T1,R>, Function2<T1,T2,R>, Function3<T1,T2,T3,R>, Function4<T1,T2,T3,T4,R>, Function5<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,R>, Function6<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,R>, Function7<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7,R>, Function8<T1,T2,T3,T4,T5,T6,T7,T8,R>

    public interface λ<R>
extends Serializable
    This is a general definition of a (checked/unchecked) function of unknown parameters and a return type R.

    A checked function may throw an exception. The exception type cannot be expressed as a generic type parameter because Java cannot calculate type bounds on function composition.

    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Daniel Dietrich

      • memoized

        λ<R> memoized()
        Returns a memoizing version of this function, which computes the return value for given arguments only one time. On subsequent calls given the same arguments the memoized value is returned.

        Please note that memoizing functions do not permit `null` as single argument or return value.

        Returns:
        a memoizing function equivalent to this.

      • isApplicableTo

        default boolean isApplicableTo(Object... objects)
        Checks if this function is applicable to the given objects, i.e. each of the given objects is either null or the object type is assignable to the parameter type.

        Please note that it is not checked if this function is defined for the given objects.

        A function is applicable to no objects by definition.

        Parameters:
        objects - Objects, may be null
        Returns:
        true, if 0 < objects.length <= arity() and this function is applicable to the given objects, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if objects is null.

      • isApplicableToTypes

        default boolean isApplicableToTypes(Class<?>... types)
        Checks if this function is generally applicable to objects of the given types.

        A function is applicable to no types by definition.

        Parameters:
        types - Argument types
        Returns:
        true, if 0 <= types.length <= arity() and this function is applicable to objects of the given types, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if types or one of the elements of types is null.
